_______________________________________________________________________________________-
Facebook uses Flexbos(css3 feature),
as we have display:block(default),
we have display:flex (default when we uses flexbox)
https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/

Notes:
	flex-direction:row (default)[in Web] BUT flex-direction:column (default)[in React/Facebook]
	If you wish to target both potrait,landscape; use flex-wrap, it will manage.
